# Creating DataFrames

## Five common ways

- **`spark.createDataFrame(data, schema)`** — list + explicit schema *(preferred)*
- **`spark.createDataFrame(data)`** — list + schema inference
- **`spark.range(n)`** — fast integer-sequence DataFrame for tests
- **`spark.createDataFrame(pandas_df)`** — round-trip from pandas
- **`spark.read.format(...).load(path)`** — from real files *(next module)*

## In practice

- **`spark.read`** dominates real pipelines
- The in-memory constructors are mostly for **tests and demos**
